[@Hyndman2014a, ch. 3., Lab Session 3]

  1. For this exercise, use the price of a dozen eggs in the United States from 19001993 (data set eggs). Experiment with the various options in the holt() function to see how much the forecasts change with damped or exponential trend. Also try changing the parameter values for alpha and beta to see how they affect the forecasts. Try to develop an intuition of what each parameter and argument is doing to the forecasts. [Hint: use h=100 when calling holt() so you can clearly see the differences between the various options when plotting the forecasts.] Which model gives the best RMSE? Do the residuals from the best model look like white noise?
library(fpp)
library(knitr)
str(eggs)
##  Time-Series [1:94] from 1900 to 1993: 277 315 315 321 315 ...
tsdisplay(eggs, plot.type="scatter") # pastebimas majimo trendas

fit1 <- holt(eggs, h=100)
#fit1$model
plot(fit1, lwd=1.5, main="alpha=0.82, beta=0.0001")   
lines(fitted(fit1), col="red")

Funkcija rekomenduoja glodinimo parametrus alpha=0.82 ir beta=0.0004. Kadangi funkcija yra viena i paprasiausi, ji prognozuoja vienod majim ir matoma logika klaida, jog kainos ateityje gyja net neigiamas reikmes, ko negali bti. Galima pabandyti skirtingas holt() funkcijos galimybes ir pairti, kaip keiiasi prognozs su damped ir exponential trendu.
Pabandysime damped trendo metod.

fit2 <- holt(eggs, h=100, damped=TRUE)
plot(fit2, lwd=1.5, main="Damped (alpha=0.84, beta=0.0001)")
lines(fitted(fit2), col="red")

Grafike - rekomenduojama prognoz su damped trendo metodu

fit2_1 <- holt(eggs, h=100, damped=TRUE, alpha=0.2)
plot(fit2_1, lwd=1.5, main="Damped (alpha=0.2, beta=0.1)")
lines(fitted(fit2_1), col="red")

Smarkiai sumainus alpha ir truput padidinus beta matoma, kad duomenys labiau suglodinami, o prognoz ilieka beveik nepakitusi.

fit2_2 <- holt(eggs, h=100, damped=TRUE, alpha=0.01)
plot(fit2_2, lwd=1.5, main="Damped (alpha=0.01, beta=0.005)")
lines(fitted(fit2_2), col="red")

Dar labiau sumainus alpha linija tampa vis labiau glodesn. Visgi pastebima, kad iais atvejais ilgame laikotarpyje nebt logika remtis damped trendo metodu, nes kainos pasiekia neigiamas reikmes.
Pabandysime exponential trendo metod.

fit3 <- holt(eggs, h=100, exponential=TRUE)
#fit3$model
plot(fit3, lwd=1.5, main="alpha=0.825, beta=0.0001")
lines(fitted(fit3), col="red")

Grafike - rekomenduojama prognoz su exponential trendo metodu. Jau prognoz atrodo logikiau, kadangi nepasiekiamos neigiamos Y aies reikms.

fit3_1 <- holt(eggs, h=100, exponential=TRUE, alpha=0.01)
plot(fit3_1, lwd=1.5, main="alpha=0.01, beta=0.0036")
lines(fitted(fit3_1), col="red")

Smarkiai sumainus alpha funkcija tapo glodesn ir pasikliautinasis intervalas ymiai susitrauk

fit3_2 <- holt(eggs, h=100, exponential=TRUE, beta=0.01)
plot(fit3_2, lwd=1.5, main="alpha=0.846, beta=0.01")
lines(fitted(fit3_2), col="red")

fit3_3 <- holt(eggs, h=100, exponential=TRUE, beta=0.03)
plot(fit3_3, lwd=1.5, main="alpha=0.85, beta=0.03")
lines(fitted(fit3_3), col="red")

I paskutinij dviej grafik pastebtina, kad vos vos padidinus beta lygmen, pasikliautinasis intervalas prasipleia kardinaliai.

  • Patikrinsime, kuris modelis duoda geriausi (t.y. maiausi) RMSE.
accuracy(fit1)[2]
## [1] 26.52594
accuracy(fit2)[2]
## [1] 26.66343
accuracy(fit2_1)[2]
## [1] 31.2163
accuracy(fit2_2)[2]
## [1] 46.63393
accuracy(fit3)[2]
## [1] 26.39044
accuracy(fit3_1)[2]
## [1] 45.39475
accuracy(fit3_2)[2]
## [1] 26.52404
accuracy(fit3_3)[2]
## [1] 26.86092

Kaip ir buvo galima tiktis, geriausiai pasirod eksponentinio trendo fit3 modelis.

  • Patikrinsime, ar liekanos i geriausio modelio yra baltasis triukmas.
Acf(fit3$res)  # grafike gana akivaizdu, kad liekanos yra baltasis triukmas

Box.test(fit3$res, fitdf=0, type="Lj") # formalus sitikinimas to nepaneigia, nes p-value > 0.05
## 
##  Box-Ljung test
## 
## data:  fit3$res
## X-squared = 0.0021, df = 1, p-value = 0.9638

2. For this exercise, use the monthly Australian short-term overseas visitors data, May 1985April 2005. (Data set: visitors.)

(a) Make a time plot of your data and describe the main features of the series.

plot(visitors)

tsdisplay(visitors, plot.type="scatter")

I grafik pastebima, kad duomenys turi ryk kasmetin sezonikum bei kylant trend.

(b) Forecast the next two years using Holt-Winters multiplicative method.

progn <- hw(visitors, seasonal="multiplicative", h=24) # h - mnesis
plot(progn)
lines(progn$fitted, col="red")

(c) Why is multiplicative seasonality necessary here?

Todl, kad multiplikatyvus metodas naudojamas, kai sezono svyravimai nra pastovs, o ia laikui bgant gijam reikmi diapazonas pleiasi.

(d) Experiment with making the trend exponential and/or damped.

progndam <- hw(visitors, seasonal="multiplicative", h=70, damped=TRUE)
plot(progndam)
lines(progndam$fitted, col="red")

prognexp <- hw(visitors, seasonal="multiplicative", h=70, exponential=TRUE)
plot(prognexp)
lines(prognexp$fitted, col="red")

Pastebtina, kad damped, prieingai nei exponential, prognozje nerodo tolimesnio augimo.

(e) Compare the RMSE of the one-step forecasts from the various methods. Which do you prefer?

accuracy(progn)[2]
## [1] 14.52211
accuracy(progndam)[2]
## [1] 14.40219
accuracy(prognexp)[2]
## [1] 14.6899

Pagal RMSE reikt rinktis damped metod.

(f) Check that the residuals from the best model look like white noise.

Acf(progndam$res)  # nors keli stulpeliai neymiai kerta pasikliautinj interval, taiau tiktina, kad liekanos yra baltasis triukmas

Box.test(progndam$res, fitdf=0, type="Lj") # formalus sitikinimas to nepaneigia
## 
##  Box-Ljung test
## 
## data:  progndam$res
## X-squared = 0.2365, df = 1, p-value = 0.6267
